<html xmlns:o='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office' xmlns:w='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40'>
      <head>
        <meta charset='utf-8'>
        <title>Daily Lesson Log</title>
        <style>
          @page WordSection1 { size: 297mm 210mm; mso-page-orientation: landscape; margin: 15mm 15mm 15mm 15mm; }
          div.WordSection1 { page: WordSection1; }
          table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; }
          td { border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top; }
          .font-bold { font-weight: bold; }
          .text-center { text-align: center; }
          .text-lg { font-size: 18px; }
          .uppercase { text-transform: uppercase; }
          .mb-6 { margin-bottom: 24px; }
          .bg-gray-100 { background-color: #f3f4f6; }
          .italic { font-style: italic; }
          .underline { text-decoration: underline; }
          .whitespace-pre-wrap { white-space: pre-wrap; }
        </style>
      </head>
      <body><div class='WordSection1'><style>
                @media print {
                  body * { visibility: hidden; }
                  .print-container, .print-container * { visibility: visible; }
                  .print-container { position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; width: 100%; }
                  @page { size: A4 landscape; margin: 10mm; }
                }
                td { vertical-align: top; }
              </style><div class="text-center mb-6"><h1 class="text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-black" style="text-align: center;">DAILY LESSON LOGS | ILAW Format</h1></div><table class="w-full border-collapse border border-black text-[11px] leading-tight text-black font-sans" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;"><colgroup><col style="width: 20%;"><col style="width: 20%;"><col style="width: 20%;"><col style="width: 20%;"><col style="width: 20%;"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold;">Name of Lesson</td><td colspan="4" class="border border-black p-2 whitespace-pre-wrap" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; white-space: pre-wrap;">1. Draw and describe regular and irregular polygons with 5, 6, 8, or 10 sides, based on measurements of sides and angles, using a ruler and protractor.
2. Draw triangles, quadrilaterals, and regular polygons (5, 6, 8, or 10 sides) with given angle measures.</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold;">Learning Area</td><td colspan="4" class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px;">Mathematics</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold;">Term and Week</td><td colspan="4" class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px;">Term 1, Week 1</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold;">Grade Level and Section</td><td colspan="4" class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px;">Grade 7 - Amethyst | Diamond | Gold | SSC</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold;">Teacher</td><td colspan="4" class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px;">Raymond G. Fradejas</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold;">No. of Sessions</td><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold text-center" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Session 1</td><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold text-center" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Session 2</td><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold text-center" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Session 3</td><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold text-center" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Session 4</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold whitespace-pre-wrap" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;">References
(books, websites, toolkits, etc.)</td><td colspan="4" class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px;">MATATAG Mathematics Curriculum Guide; DepEd Order No. 009, s. 2026; DepEd-approved Grade 7 Mathematics learning resources.</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 font-bold whitespace-pre-wrap" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-weight: bold; white-space: pre-wrap;">Declaration of AI use
Cite how AI was used in the formulation of the lesson plan.</td><td colspan="4" class="border border-black p-2 italic" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; font-style: italic;">3.5 Thinking AI was utilized to unpack the competencies, format the lesson plan, ensure alignment with DepEd MATATAG 3-Term guidelines, generate instructional vector graphics, and create structured formative assessments based on the provided inputs. See DO 3, 2026 Annex A.</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 align-top" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong class="text-sm" style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;">Intentions.</strong><br><br><span class="italic text-[10px]" style="font-size: 10px; font-style: italic;">Meaningful learning experiences are anchored in how we frame them. Start by deciding what you want learners to master by the end of the lesson - keep it clear and simple. Remember: Understanding your learners' evolving context and designing around it help ensure that your lessons connect with and are relevant to them.</span></td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Content Standard:</strong><br>The learners should have knowledge and understanding of regular and irregular polygons and their features/properties.<br><br><strong>Performance Standard:</strong><br>By the end of the term, the learners are able to draw, and describe the features/properties of, regular and irregular polygons.<br><br><strong>Learning Competency:</strong><br>Draw and describe regular and irregular polygons.<br><br><strong>Session Objective:</strong><br>Identify and describe the features of regular and irregular polygons based on visual properties and initial measurements.</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Content Standard:</strong><br>The learners should have knowledge and understanding of regular and irregular polygons and their features/properties.<br><br><strong>Performance Standard:</strong><br>By the end of the term, the learners are able to draw, and describe the features/properties of, regular and irregular polygons.<br><br><strong>Learning Competency:</strong><br>1. Draw and describe regular and irregular polygons with 5, 6, 8, or 10 sides, based on measurements of sides and angles, using a ruler and protractor.<br><br><strong>Session Objective:</strong><br>Session 2 Objective: Deepen understanding of target concepts and applications.</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Content Standard:</strong><br>The learners should have knowledge and understanding of regular and irregular polygons and their features/properties.<br><br><strong>Performance Standard:</strong><br>By the end of the term, the learners are able to draw, and describe the features/properties of, regular and irregular polygons.<br><br><strong>Learning Competency:</strong><br>1. Draw and describe regular and irregular polygons with 5, 6, 8, or 10 sides, based on measurements of sides and angles, using a ruler and protractor.<br><br><strong>Session Objective:</strong><br>Session 3 Objective: Deepen understanding of target concepts and applications.</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Content Standard:</strong><br>The learners should have knowledge and understanding of regular and irregular polygons and their features/properties.<br><br><strong>Performance Standard:</strong><br>By the end of the term, the learners are able to draw, and describe the features/properties of, regular and irregular polygons.<br><br><strong>Learning Competency:</strong><br>1. Draw and describe regular and irregular polygons with 5, 6, 8, or 10 sides, based on measurements of sides and angles, using a ruler and protractor.<br><br><strong>Session Objective:</strong><br>Session 4 Objective: Deepen understanding of target concepts and applications.</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 align-top" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong class="text-sm" style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;">Learning Experiences.</strong><br><br><span class="italic text-[10px]" style="font-size: 10px; font-style: italic;">How will we get there? Includes pre-lesson, lesson proper, and post-lesson. The learning experiences are structured using the ESRU (Elicit, Student Response, Recognize, Use) cycle to ensure active engagement and formative assessment at every step.</span></td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Pre-Lesson (15 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Look around the classroom. Can you point to a shape that has straight sides?</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> The blackboard is a rectangle! The clock is a circle.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Good spotting. The blackboard is indeed a polygon, but the clock is not because it doesn't have straight sides.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Today, we will focus on these closed shapes with straight sides called polygons.</div></div></div><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Lesson Proper (25 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Using your ruler, measure the sides of shape A (square) and shape B (rectangle). What did you find?</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> Shape A has all sides equal. Shape B has two long sides and two short sides.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Accurate measurements. This equality in sides is a key feature we will use.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Let's formally define what makes a polygon 'regular' versus 'irregular' based on these measurements.</div></div></div></td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Pre-Lesson (10 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Review concepts from Session 1.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> Students share previous learnings.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Validate correct recall.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Connect to today's specific activity.</div></div></div><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Lesson Proper (30 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Let's practice these concepts with new problem sets.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> Students collaborate on solving.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Check for accuracy and understanding.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Demonstrate proper techniques and formulas.</div></div></div></td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Pre-Lesson (10 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Review concepts from Session 2.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> Students share previous learnings.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Validate correct recall.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Connect to today's specific activity.</div></div></div><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Lesson Proper (30 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Let's practice these concepts with new problem sets.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> Students collaborate on solving.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Check for accuracy and understanding.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Demonstrate proper techniques and formulas.</div></div></div></td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Pre-Lesson (10 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Review concepts from Session 3.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> Students share previous learnings.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Validate correct recall.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Connect to today's specific activity.</div></div></div><div class="mb-4 last:mb-0" style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong class="underline" style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Lesson Proper (30 mins)</strong><br><div class="mt-1 space-y-1" style="margin-top: 4px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Elicit:</strong> Let's practice these concepts with new problem sets.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Student Response:</strong> Students collaborate on solving.</div><div style="margin-bottom: 4px;"><strong>Teacher Recognizes:</strong> Check for accuracy and understanding.</div><div><strong>Teacher Uses:</strong> Demonstrate proper techniques and formulas.</div></div></div></td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 align-top" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong class="text-sm" style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;">Assessing Learning.</strong><br><br><span class="italic text-[10px]" style="font-size: 10px; font-style: italic;">How do we know they learned? Formative Assessment: Create a task, activity, or questions to evaluate learning and provide feedback. Include ways for learners to ask for guidance or support.</span></td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Formative Assessment:</strong><br>Polygon Sorting Activity: Learners classify 10 paper cutouts into regular and irregular polygons. [Learner AI Use Category: Prohibited].</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Formative Assessment:</strong><br>Formative Assessment: Practice worksheet 2.</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Formative Assessment:</strong><br>Formative Assessment: Practice worksheet 3.</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Formative Assessment:</strong><br>Formative Assessment: Practice worksheet 4.</td></tr><tr><td class="border border-black p-2 align-top" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong class="text-sm" style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;">Ways Forward.</strong><br><br><span class="italic text-[10px]" style="font-size: 10px; font-style: italic;">Meaningful learning can also happen beyond the classroom - for both the learners and the teacher. Pause and reflect on what happened today.</span></td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Extended learning opportunities:</strong><br>Home/community polygon hunt; create two examples and one non-example.<br><br><strong>Reflections:</strong><br>Teacher reflection: What went well? What evidence showed understanding? What needs adjustment?</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Extended learning opportunities:</strong><br>Identify related real-world applications in the community.<br><br><strong>Reflections:</strong><br>Teacher reflection for Session 2: Assess group collaboration and understanding.</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Extended learning opportunities:</strong><br>Identify related real-world applications in the community.<br><br><strong>Reflections:</strong><br>Teacher reflection for Session 3: Assess group collaboration and understanding.</td><td class="border border-black p-2" style="border: 1px solid black; padding: 6px; vertical-align: top;"><strong>Extended learning opportunities:</strong><br>Identify related real-world applications in the community.<br><br><strong>Reflections:</strong><br>Teacher reflection for Session 4: Assess group collaboration and understanding.</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="mt-8 flex justify-between text-[11px] text-black w-3/4" style="margin-top: 32px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; width: 75%;"><div class="w-1/2" style="width: 50%;"><p class="mb-6" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Prepared by:</p><p class="font-bold underline uppercase" style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline; text-transform: uppercase;">Raymond G. Fradejas</p><p>Teacher II</p></div><div class="w-1/2" style="width: 50%;"><p class="mb-6" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Checked by:</p><p class="font-bold underline uppercase" style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline; text-transform: uppercase;">SDFSDFSD</p><p>Master Teacher III</p></div></div></div></body></html>